<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E887F9EBD164F641" blockId="37.[151,1077,1556,1584]" box="[151,1077,1556,1584]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
65. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999238551E8D1F9EAD60BF65E" authority="(Fallen, 1823) (Dolichopodinae)" authorityName="Dolichopodinae" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[193,858,1556,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D1F9EAD7DEF641" bold="true" box="[193,655,1556,1583]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D1F9EAD4B4F641" bold="true" box="[193,485,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Hercostomus nigripennis</emphasis>
(Fallén, 1823)
</emphasis>
(Dolichopodinae)
</taxonomicName>
— 
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551EB68F9EAD164F641" bold="true" box="[888,1077,1557,1583]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
new to 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EBDDF9EAD164F641" box="[973,1077,1557,1583]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350B2B199238551E887F9A7D495F7FC" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E887F9A7D77FF61C" blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" box="[151,558,1623,1650]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E887F9A7D743F61C" bold="true" box="[151,530,1623,1650]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7F984D4AAF6D4" blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7F984D430F6F8" bold="true" box="[199,353,1659,1686]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe, largely lacking in the south and southeast (except for 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EC57F984D12EF6F8" box="[1095,1151,1659,1686]" name="Italy" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Italy</collectingCountry>
). 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EC86F984D1A8F6FB" box="[1174,1273,1659,1685]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one province (Trás-os-Montes e Alto Douro).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7F93BD463F724" blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7F93BD47DF6B0" bold="true" box="[199,300,1732,1758]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecology.</emphasis>
The only sampling site of this species in 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EB17F93CD637F6B3" box="[775,870,1731,1757]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
were permanent pastures (Lameiros) bordered by 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999238551E887F917D45AF76C" box="[151,267,1768,1794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E887F917D5B1F76C" box="[151,224,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Betula</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, and an ancient bog that was drained in the 20th century for cultivation. In northwestern Europe, this species is restricted to open oligotrophic biotopes where it can be found in numbers on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999238551ECF2F8F3D47FF724" authority="(Pollet 2000)" authorityName="Pollet" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Pollet" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Potentilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erecta">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551ECF2F8F3D0CDF74B" box="[1250,1436,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Potentilla erecta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB9CCB99238551E88FF8D0D477F724" author="Pollet, M." box="[159,294,1839,1866]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7F8ACD7EEF700" blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" box="[199,703,1875,1902]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7F8ACD400F700" bold="true" box="[199,337,1875,1902]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
1.1 (very rare). Fairly rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7F888D495F7FC" blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" box="[199,452,1911,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7F888D4D3F7FC" bold="true" box="[199,386,1911,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Activity period.</emphasis>
June.
</paragraph>
